  "prompt": "Google Nexus 7: How to change default action for playing video from Engadget app? I have chosen YouTube but it doesn't play. My HTC One X uses streaming media player. How to change this default action to streaming media player?",
  "response": "To change the default action for playing videos on your Google Nexus 7 from the Engadget app, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Clear Default Preferences:**\n   - Go to **Settings** on your Nexus 7.\n   - Scroll down and select **Apps** or **Applications**.\n   - Find the **Engadget app** in the list and tap on it.\n   - Look for the section labeled **Launch by default** or **Default apps**.\n   - Tap on **Clear defaults** if this option is available. This will reset any default actions associated with the app.\n\n2. **Play a Video Again:**\n   - Go back to the Engadget app and try to play a video again. This time, you should see a prompt asking you to select the app you want to use to play the video.\n\n3. **Select Your Desired App:**\n   - When prompted to choose an app, select **Streaming Media Player** (or whichever media player you'd like to use).\n   - Make sure to check the option that says **Always** if you want to set this option as the default for future video playback.\n\n4. **Test Again:**\n   - Play another video to ensure your settings took effect and that the video now plays in the Streaming Media Player.\n\nIf you still encounter issues, you may want to verify that the Streaming Media Player is properly installed and that it supports the video format being played.",
